The excess molar volume , calculated from the density data, provides the temperature dependence of  in the temperature range (293.15 to 353.15) K. Partial molar volumes and excess partial molar volumes of two components were also calculated. It was found that the  in the systems studied increase with rising temperature.
Citation.sTitle: Densities and volumetric properties of binary mixtures of xylene with N,N-dimethylformamide at different temperatures
